    <bodyTop>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p><strong><span class="lead"><img src="?width=777&amp;height=278&amp;mode=max" alt="Three images of QMU" width="777" height="278" data-udi="umb://media/e0a63e58aa2c4712946320a2e4400a99" /></span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span class="lead">Head of Division, Nursing, Paramedic Science, Occupational Therapy and Arts Therapies</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"> </p>
<p><strong><span class="lead">Responsible to:</span> </strong>Dean, School of Health Sciences</p>
<p><span class="lead">Responsible for:</span> Management and leadership of the Division</p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Grade:</strong></span> Grade 10</p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Salary:</strong> </span>An attractive and competitive starting at £61,818. This is negotiable for the right candidate. Potential to offer a Professorship if successful applicant matches the relevant criteria.</p>
<p><strong><span class="lead">Hours: </span></strong>The working hours for the position of Head of Division are notionally 35 hours per week which equates to 1.0 FTE.  Time devoted should be as reasonably necessary to fulfil the duties of the post. </p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Location: </strong></span>Contractual place of work will be our QMU Campus in Musselburgh. The University is currently trialling hybrid working so it is expected that the role holder will have a balance of on-campus and working from home.</p>]]></Value>
    </bodyTop>
    <centralBlocks>
      <Value><![CDATA[[
  {
    "key": "6e606616-d424-48fb-a616-ee4194ad1fde",
    "name": "Our Purpose",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Our Purpose",
    "content": "<p>We see our purpose as helping to create a better society through education, research and innovation, and by providing a supportive and creative learning environment in which students and staff can thrive.</p>\n<p>In seeking to fulfil this purpose, we are clear and realistic about our strengths, focused on strategic goals, persistent in pursuing opportunities and overcoming barriers, and guided by our values.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "b4d09376-d804-4db4-8282-1b72bceed2c9",
    "name": "Our Values",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Our Values",
    "content": "<p>We are a university that is modern in our outlook and facilities but with a maturity built on a long history of serving the community, both locally and globally, and enhancing its wellbeing. We work in a transparent and inclusive manner and hold to core values in everything we do.</p>\n<p>We value <strong>social justice</strong>: In fact, it underpins our world view. We embrace equality, diversity, inclusion, respect, and supporting our communities. Opportunities and access are open to all and on a fair basis.</p>\n<p>We value <strong>environmental sustainability</strong>: We recognise the severe threats to our environment and will be a sector leader in response. Our modern campus is a great asset in this work.</p>\n<p>We value<strong> the individual</strong> and encourage collective support: Each member of staff and each student has their own journey to make and their own contribution to give. Queen Margaret University provides the supportive environment to facilitate this.</p>\n<p>We value<strong> intellectual curiosity and the journey of discovery</strong>: We design our teaching and research to facilitate this.</p>\n<p>We value<strong> ambition</strong>: We inspire our students and staff to achieve the best that they can. We pursue opportunities, often in partnership and collaboration with others, to transform and influence society for the better and enhance our visibility within the higher education sector and the wider economy.</p>\n<p>We value <strong>excellence</strong>: This is embedded in our research, teaching and learning, knowledge exchange and the services we provide. It will be exemplified in the experience of our students, staff and partners.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "d4ba4410-39a3-4cbf-bbb6-8db64ea461e5",
    "name": "Our commitment to Equality, Diversity and Inclusion",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Our commitment to Equality, Diversity and Inclusion",
    "content": "<p>One of the values at the heart of <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"/{localLink:umb://media/f03bca84f7dd4b09a01d73795da2ab67}\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Qmu Our Strategic Plan 2025\">our strategic plan</a> is our commitment to social justice and equality, diversity and inclusion.</p>\n<p>We are committed to creating an environment where diversity is celebrated, we can all be ourselves and everyone is treated fairly, regardless of sex, disability, ethnic origin, religion or belief, sexual orientation, marital or transgender status, pregnancy/maternity or age.</p>\n<p>As set out in our <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"/{localLink:umb://media/9d6e93e1e8f54b7a867bcce869c55280}\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Equality Policy\">Equality Policy</a>, all staff and students have rights and responsibilities in relation to the promotion of equality, which is central to our staff development activities.</p>\n<p>We are fully committed to both meeting and exceeding our obligations under current equalities legislation. Specialist staff networks, regular communications and events are just some of the ways in which we keep our community connected and engaged with diversity issues.</p>\n<p>We have a genuine commitment to equality of opportunity for our staff and students, and we strive to employ a workforce that reflects the communities we serve.</p>\n<p>We particularly encourage applications from people from a Minority Ethnic background, who are underrepresented at the University.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "d58f2617-43aa-4f1d-8ab9-8f92c979cfea",
    "name": "The role",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "The role",
    "content": "<p>The Head of Division's role will manage and lead the advancement of our work in interdisciplinary healthcare education and collaborative partnerships, by further developing the nursing, paramedic science, occupational therapy and arts therapies strategic focus at QMU with a particular focus on person-centred practice and person-centred research.</p>\n<p>The role of the Head of Division has been actively working at developing a person-centred culture for all staff and students through a Shared Governance model of working, supported by a distributive/collective leadership model. The role of the Head of Division in this structure has a primary focus of enabling this distributive/collective leadership model of working and maintaining responsibility for specific functions as required by the university. </p>\n<p>The Head of Division along with the Deputy Head of Divisions form the Leadership Team for the Divisions.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "d6fdbddf-cfba-40dc-8993-d938a42767ad",
    "name": "What you'll do",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "What you'll do",
    "content": "<ul>\n<li>Provide strategic leadership, insight, in-depth knowledge and vision for the Divisions that will support the University to deliver its strategic goals in regard to academic development, student learning and research.</li>\n<li>Enhance the profile of the Divisions in international fora and relevant local and national networks through internationally significant academic leadership.</li>\n<li>Lead, manage and develop a team of staff to effectively manage and co-ordinate all aspects of the implementation of the School operational plan in relation to nursing, occupational therapy and arts therapies.</li>\n<li>Manage the Divisional budget, ensuring that future developments are planned for, costed and included.</li>\n<li>In partnership with the Deputy Head of Division of Nursing &amp; Paramedic Science and the Deputy Head of Division of Occupational Therapy and Arts Therapies to continue to develop and sustain the divisional culture and values.</li>\n<li>Be an active member of the research community in The Centre for Person-centred Practice Research (www.cpcpr.org); working in partnership with the Centre Director. Progress own research programme consistent with Queen Margaret University’s Research Strategy and the priorities of The Centre for Person-centred Practice Research. Lead and undertake rigorous and systematic research and development studies with uni-disciplinary and multidisciplinary colleagues and publish research findings in high quality peer-reviewed journals</li>\n<li>Collaborate with existing research in the Divisions and the School of Health Sciences, complementing the research of other members of the academic community and in so doing enhance the University’s research capability and credibility. Lead the building of research and development capacity and capability across all subject areas.</li>\n<li>Lead innovative curriculum development, management, marketing and research at pre, post-registration and postgraduate levels.</li>\n<li>Actively promote nursing, occupational therapy and arts therapies and engage with statutory and voluntary services, service users and other members of the interdisciplinary team to enhance subject development.</li>\n<li>Undertake administrative, management and other duties as agreed with the Dean of School of Health Sciences and any other duties appropriate to the grade and nature of the post.</li>\n<li>Participate in the corporate activities of the staff group within and outwith the University.</li>\n</ul>"
  },
  {
    "key": "cfdada30-b3d5-4bfe-a525-9120e85b1971",
    "name": "What you'll bring",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "What you'll bring",
    "content": "<ul>\n<li>You will be an accomplished academic with a successful track record in the broad field of Nursing, Paramedic Science, Occupational Therapy and Arts Therapies with demonstrable experience in management, learning, and in research leadership.</li>\n<li>\n<p>You will be a strong motivator and influencer with a proven track record in research leadership development and grant generation.</p>\n</li>\n<li>You will be in a discipline relevant to this role.</li>\n</ul>"
  },
  {
    "key": "0f8ad149-ae05-4a41-89e1-7ad788b42cb7",
    "name": "The rewards",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "The rewards",
    "content": "<p>We pride ourselves on providing a working environment where staff can flourish and thrive as part of our QMU community.</p>\n<p>Alongside an attractive salary, there are a number of <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/3298a62bbe1c471cac8071bfbbdf969d}\" title=\"Working Life at QMU\"> benefits</a> that we provide to our people.</p>\n<p>We know that work/life balance is important so we are open to considering Flexible Working options.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "3c5cca43-cc17-4e76-8828-2c99880eaf8b",
    "name": "Where you'll work",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Where you'll work",
    "content": "<p>Contractual place of work will be our QMU Campus in Musselburgh. The University is currently trialling hybrid working so it is expected that the role holder will have a balance of on-campus and working from home.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "51670ab1-55ca-4d55-a1df-37cdce0de7c1",
    "name": "Recruitment, Onboarding and Induction Process & Timescales",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Recruitment, Onboarding and Induction Process & Timescales",
    "content": "<p>To apply please send your CV and covering letter detailing how you meet the criteria for the role to <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"mailto:recruitment@qmu.ac.uk\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Recruitment Email\">recruitment@qmu.ac.uk</a>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Our timescales are set out below:</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Application closing date: <span>9th </span><span>May 2022 </span></p>\n<p>Interview date: 20th May 2022</p>\n<p>*please note these dates may be subject to change</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Through our interview process we do our best to ensure candidates get a real sense of both the role they have applied for and the University.</p>\n<p>We will ask you competency-based questions in relation to the role; however we also hope to learn about you during our time together at interview.</p>\n<p>For this role, interviews will be held in person, at our Campus in Musselburgh.</p>\n<p>For the successful candidate, we pride ourselves on providing a thorough and welcoming onbaording and induction process. Our induction process is designed to help people feel part of our QMU community.</p>\n<p>Our induction process includes a session with our Principal and Vice Chancellor where you will meet other new staff members and hear more about our values, strategy and who we are, and you will also have an HR induction session and tailored local induction plan led by your line manager.</p>\n<p>If you would like to speak to us informally about the role please contact Professor Fiona Coutts, Dean, School of Health Sciences via email at <a rel=\"noopener\" href=\"mailto:fcoutts@qmu.ac.uk\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Email Fiona Coutts\">fcoutts@qmu.ac.uk</a></p>"
  }
]]]></Value>
